observations.recommendation:
11. Reclassify to the appropriate PPE accounts all completed projects still carried in the Construction in Progress accounts based on the Status Report of the Municipal Engineer and the accounting records on projects with final payments;
12. Evaluate the dormant amounts in the Construction in Progress accounts based on the nature of the transaction and on the Status Report of the Municipal Engineer and prepare the adjusting entries to reclassify the CIP to either an asset or an expense;
13. Prepare the necessary adjusting entries on the negative balance in the CIP account;
14. Henceforth, transfer the cost of completed projects, from Construction in Progress account, to the appropriate asset account immediately upon payment of final billing to the contractor. At the same time, record the corresponding depreciation expense on the related PPE account.

26. Send confirmation letters to the Government Agencies which transferred funds to the LGU in previous years to determine whether the LGU still have payables for liquidation to the said agencies. In case there are unliquidated fund transfers, return the unutilized amounts immediately;
27. Trace back prior accounting entries in the Due to NGA account to determine the composition of the account and the causes of the negative balances of ₱1,441,685.06 and prepare the adjusting entries, where necessary;
28. Return to the Bureau of Treasury the balances from fund transfers in prior years, regardless of the source agency;
29. Maintain complete subsidiary records for each source agency and retain copies of MOA and such other documents for every funds received from NGAs.

37. Prepare lapsing schedules to compute the correct depreciation and Accumulated Depreciation of properties under PPE;
38. Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the gross carrying amount of any fully depreciated PPE that is still in use.
39. Record an Allowance for Impairment Loss on the Market and on other depreciable PPEs and disclose necessary information in the notes.
